y plan released=C2=A0the Sacklers from liability, and the bankruptcy judge =
approved it, is that=C2=A0<em>their assets were probably already shielded</=
em>, in offshore spendthrift trusts that creditors probably couldn=E2=80=99=
t touch. That does seem bad! But getting rid of third-party releases in ban=
kruptcy doesn=E2=80=99t fix it.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And note th=
at the result of this ruling is not that they go back to the negotiating ta=
ble and the Sacklers kick in, you know, $8 billion instead of $4.5 billion.=
 The result of this ruling is that the whole settlement framework is illega=
